description:'\x3cp\x3eUse the \x3ca href\x3d"#/p5/beginContour"\x3ebeginContour()\x3c/a\x3e and \x3ca href\x3d"#/p5/endContour"\x3eendContour()\x3c/a\x3e functions to create negative\nshapes within shapes such as the center of the letter \x26#39;O\x26#39;. \x3ca href\x3d"#/p5/beginContour"\x3ebeginContour()\x3c/a\x3e\nbegins recording vertices for the shape and \x3ca href\x3d"#/p5/endContour"\x3eendContour()\x3c/a\x3e stops recording.\nThe vertices that define a negative shape must \x26quot;wind\x26quot; in the opposite\ndirection from the exterior shape. First draw vertices for the exterior\nclockwise order, then for internal shapes, draw vertices\nshape in counter-clockwise.\n\x3cbr\x3e\x3cbr\x3e\nThese functions can only be used within a \x3ca href\x3d"#/p5/beginShape"\x3ebeginShape()\x3c/a\x3e/\x3ca href\x3d"#/p5/endShape"\x3eendShape()\x3c/a\x3e pair and\ntransformations such as \x3ca href\x3d"#/p5/translate"\x3etranslate()\x3c/a\x3e, \x3ca href\x3d"#/p5/rotate"\x3erotate()\x3c/a\x3e, and \x3ca href\x3d"#/p5/scale"\x3escale()\x3c/a\x3e do not work\nwithin a \x3ca href\x3d"#/p5/beginContour"\x3ebeginContour()\x3c/a\x3e/\x3ca href\x3d"#/p5/endContour"\x3eendContour()\x3c/a\x3e pair. It is also not possible to use\nother shapes, such as \x3ca href\x3d"#/p5/ellipse"\x3eellipse()\x3c/a\x3e or \x3ca href\x3d"#/p5/rect"\x3erect()\x3c/a\x3e within.\x3c/p\x3e\n',
itemtype:"method",name:"endContour",chainable:1,example:["\n\x3cdiv\x3e\n\x3ccode\x3e\ntranslate(50, 50);\nstroke(255, 0, 0);\nbeginShape();\n// Exterior part of shape, clockwise winding\nvertex(-40, -40);\nvertex(40, -40);\nvertex(40, 40);\nvertex(-40, 40);\n// Interior part of shape, counter-clockwise winding\nbeginContour();\nvertex(-20, -20);\nvertex(-20, 20);\nvertex(20, 20);\nvertex(20, -20);\nendContour();\nendShape(CLOSE);\n\x3c/code\x3e\n\x3c/div\x3e"],alt:"white rect and smaller grey rect with red outlines in center of canvas.",
